</figure>

<figure id="Figure_17_02_Grating3">
<media id="fs-id1167066012716" alt="(a) Graph labeled “double slit.” A sine curve with three peaks is plotted with its troughs on a horizontal axis. Three points on the axis are labeled, corresponding to three maxima. Left to right, the points are labeled “m equals 1,” m equals zero,” and “m equals 1.” (b) Graph labeled “grating.” A curve with three tall narrow peaks is plotted with its troughs on a horizontal axis. On either side of the three peaks are two much smaller peaks (the larger peaks are separated by a total of four smaller peaks). Three points on the axis are labeled, corresponding to three maxima. Left to right, the points are labeled “m equals 1,” m equals zero,” and “m equals 1.”">
