<section id="fs-id1167065878071" class="concept"><title>Concept Items</title><exercise id="fs-id1167065946888"><problem id="fs-id1167064535386">
<para id="fs-id1167064535388">There is a principle related to resolution that is expressed by this equation.
</para>
<equation id="eip-idm230410704"> <m:math><m:mrow>
<m:mi>θ</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac><m:mi>λ</m:mi><m:mi>D</m:mi></m:mfrac>
</m:mrow></m:math> </equation>
<para id="eip-idm223576880">What is that principle stated in full?</para>
